docs.abstract: Robots are struggling to cope with the real world. Lately, so are Twitter, Google, Facebook and a few other companies.
docs.snippet: Robots are struggling to cope with the real world. Lately, so are Twitter, Google, Facebook and a few other companies.
docs.lead_paragraph: Each week, technology reporters and columnists from The New York Times review the week’s news, offering analysis and maybe a joke or two about the most important developments in the tech industry. Want this newsletter in your inbox? Sign up here.

headline.main: The Week in Tech: The Robots Aren’t as Human as They Seem
headline.print_headline: Robots Are Improving Quickly, But They Can Still Be Dumb

docs.abstract: The Supreme Court said the Aadhaar fingerprint ID system is legal, but restricted it to government benefits and banned companies from using it.
docs.snippet: The Supreme Court said the Aadhaar fingerprint ID system is legal, but restricted it to government benefits and banned companies from using it.
docs.lead_paragraph: MUMBAI, India — In a landmark ruling on Wednesday, India’s Supreme Court placed strict limits on the government’s national biometric identity system while also finding that the sweeping program did not fundamentally violate the privacy rights of the country’s 1.3 billion residents.

headline.main: India’s Top Court Limits Sweep of Biometric ID Program
headline.print_headline: Reining In a Digital ID System

docs.abstract: The anonymous group’s campaign highlights Facebook’s continuing trouble with political advertising.
docs.snippet: The anonymous group’s campaign highlights Facebook’s continuing trouble with political advertising.
docs.lead_paragraph: LONDON — Prime Minister Theresa May has struggled to build support for her plan for Britain’s exit from the European Union. Now, it turns out, some of the opposition has come from an unknown organization posting ads to millions of people on Facebook.

headline.main: Facebook Ads From Unknown Backer Take Aim at Brexit Plan
headline.print_headline: Mystery Group Barrages British Facebook Users With Brexit Ads

docs.abstract: The company reported a net income of $2.9 billion in the third quarter, partly by being more efficient in its warehouses and data centers.
docs.snippet: The company reported a net income of $2.9 billion in the third quarter, partly by being more efficient in its warehouses and data centers.
docs.lead_paragraph: Amazon’s profits were hit or miss for its first couple of decades. But now, for the first time, they are starting to look consistent — with four consecutive quarters above $1 billion in profit.

headline.main: Amazon Squeezes Out More Profit as Sales Growth Slows
headline.print_headline: Sales Slow, But Amazon Clears Profit Of $1 Billion

docs.abstract: Mr. Bezos and his wife, MacKenzie, made what was by far their largest political contribution to the With Honor Fund, which backs congressional candidates with military backgrounds.
docs.snippet: Mr. Bezos and his wife, MacKenzie, made what was by far their largest political contribution to the With Honor Fund, which backs congressional candidates with military backgrounds.
docs.lead_paragraph: Jeff Bezos, the founder of Amazon and the richest man in the world, has recently faced the ire of elected officials across the political spectrum, President Trump on the right and Senator Bernie Sanders on the left.

headline.print_headline: Bezos Giving $10 Million To Help Elect Veterans

docs.abstract: A year after a public relations debacle over pay disparities between its male and female stars, the British broadcaster released salary data that showed halting progress in wage equity.
docs.snippet: A year after a public relations debacle over pay disparities between its male and female stars, the British broadcaster released salary data that showed halting progress in wage equity.
docs.lead_paragraph: A year after a public relations debacle over wide pay disparities between its male and female stars, the BBC on Wednesday released a new  list detailing how much it pays its top talent. And while the list suggested that there had been some progress, the reality remains somewhat gloomy for women.

headline.main: BBC Closes Gender Pay Gap, but Men Are Still Its 12 Highest-Paid Stars
headline.print_headline: BBC Closes Gender Gap, but Men Still Top Pay List

docs.abstract: The Supreme Court nominee Brett Kavanaugh and some high school friends described themselves in a yearbook as “Renate” alumni. The woman they were referring to is furious.
docs.snippet: The Supreme Court nominee Brett Kavanaugh and some high school friends described themselves in a yearbook as “Renate” alumni. The woman they were referring to is furious.
docs.lead_paragraph: Brett Kavanaugh’s page in his high school yearbook offers a glimpse of the teenage years of the man who is now President Trump’s Supreme Court nominee: lots of football, plenty of drinking, parties at the beach. Among the reminiscences about sports and booze is a mysterious entry: “Renate Alumnius.”

headline.main: Kavanaugh’s Yearbook Page Is ‘Horrible, Hurtful’ to a Woman It Named

byline.original: By Kate Kelly and David Enrich

docs.abstract: Cody Wilson, a gun rights and free speech advocate, will be allowed to post online tutorials for 3-D printing firearms, sparking concerns about so-called ghost guns.
docs.snippet: Cody Wilson, a gun rights and free speech advocate, will be allowed to post online tutorials for 3-D printing firearms, sparking concerns about so-called ghost guns.
docs.lead_paragraph: Learning to make a so-called ghost gun — an untraceable, unregistered firearm without a serial number — could soon become much easier.

headline.main: ‘Downloadable Gun’ Clears a Legal Obstacle, and Activists Are Alarmed
headline.print_headline: ‘Downloadable Gun’ Clears a Legal Obstacle, Alarming Some Activists
